		<item>
		<title>UIC celebrates Trans Awareness Week</title>
		<link>https://today.uic.edu/uic-celebrates-trans-awareness-week/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[UIC News contributor]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 09 Nov 2022 14:50:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Announcements]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Info]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://today.uic.edu/?p=138683&#038;preview=true&#038;preview_id=138683</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[UIC's Chancellor’s Committee on the Status of LGBTQ+ People and the Gender and Sexuality Center will celebrate Trans Awareness Week Nov. 13-19]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>UIC&#8217;s Chancellor’s Committee on the Status of LGBTQ+ People and the Gender and Sexuality Center will celebrate <a href="https://www.glaad.org/transweek">Trans Awareness Week</a> Nov. 13-19.</p>
<p>To commemorate Trans Awareness Week this year, the GSC wants to share the voices and experiences of our trans siblings. They will be creating a video to highlight all of the wonderful ways that trans people find and build community, and what exactly &#8220;community&#8221; means to them. Please submit your <a href="https://forms.uofi.uic.edu/sec/391402265?referrer=">written response</a> or <a href="https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Fdrive%2Ffolders%2F1xsf32dh4I_s7iOqIOlFfKJbAIXS9a-Wj%3Fusp%3Dsharing&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjflamm82%40uic.edu%7C83123b39ad5b44d3cedb08dabdd2115f%7Ce202cd477a564baa99e3e3b71a7c77dd%7C0%7C0%7C638031007179381856%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=OAIW7ta%2F7SASGAkWuB4B2oY0W5DkUweidr%2Bcn9w%2BRcY%3D&amp;reserved=0">digital content</a>. You can also stop by the GSC during open hours to record your responses with their staff. If you align with the Trans community and have any art or music you would like to highlight, please include it in your submission.</p>
<p>The Chancellor’s Committee on the Status of LGBTQ+ People encourages all UIC community members to learn more about LGBTQ+ folx and reinforces our commitment to greater inclusion of LGBTQ+ individuals at UIC with the following resources:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://gsc.uic.edu/">UIC Gender and Sexuality Center.</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://gsc.uic.edu/inclusion/all-gender-restrooms/">All-Gender Restrooms.</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>UIC Bias Reporting Tool: <a href="https://dos.uic.edu/diversity-education/bias-reporting-prevention/">Bias Reporting and Prevention.</a></li>
<li><a href="https://it.uic.edu/services-support/student-resources/password-and-netid/preferred-name-and-personal-pronouns/">Update your preferred name and personal pronouns</a> in Banner and on <a href="https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.zoom.us%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Farticles%2F4402698027533-Adding-and-sharing-your-pronouns&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjflamm82%40uic.edu%7C7e11e9cb63184f1387b008da62cb58ca%7Ce202cd477a564baa99e3e3b71a7c77dd%7C0%7C0%7C637930922781695054%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=lkETs56YJpbSAPh0aygLGc4rMAvNESEST0t0Lr0MIv0%3D&amp;reserved=0">Zoom</a>.
<ul>
<li>We know that pronouns can change and UIC community members are welcome to update as needed.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>For allies: <a href="https://gsc.uic.edu/allyship/">Navigating Allyship.</a></li>
<li>For faculty:
<ul>
<li>Make use of <a href="https://teaching.uic.edu/resources/teaching-guides/engaged-teaching-strategies/">engaged teaching strategies</a> to foster interaction with students.</li>
<li>Ask your students what they’d prefer to be called and make a note on your roster.</li>
<li><strong>Coming Soon:</strong> Center for the Advancement of Teaching Excellence <a href="https://teaching.uic.edu/resources/teaching-guides/inclusive-equity-minded-teaching-practices/">Pronoun Usage.</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
